software.leonov.common.util.function

Interface CheckedIntSupplier

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface CheckedIntSupplier
    Mirror of the IntSupplier interface whose getAsInt() method can throw a checked exception.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Static Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      int getAsInt()
      Returns an integer result.
      static IntSupplier unchecked(CheckedIntSupplier supplier)
      Returns an IntSupplier which delegates to the underlying CheckedIntSupplier, rethrowing any checked exceptions as if they were unchecked.
      static int uncheckedGet(CheckedIntSupplier supplier)
      Returns the result of calling getAsInt() on the specified CheckedIntSupplier rethrowing any checked exceptions as if they were unchecked.
